snippet.textDisplay:
It was such a joy to watch....I just totally got absorbed for 1 hour.....from the scene when smiff and gavalar walk in on dawny pete pam and mick stoned out of their trees rocking around to Dreadlock Holiday to the poignant scene by Marco's with Stace giving Gavarindeeni a reality check was cracking and the Paolo Nutini song playback from their first night was a nice touch.......
The detail too like when smiff is opening presents for baby Neil in front of Nessa and she gives him a knowing look when he puts his foot down about being too young to play certain video games. She knows Smiff is a good dad. Did anybody spot that baby Neil had wrapped his dads present up in foil.....you just scrunch and done!
I think all fans were with pam and the gang about not liking Laura and the way she dissed his size......we dont like Laura.......
But I bet there wasnt a single fan who preficted the ending......blew me away. Overall they did a cracking job. Lets hope we see more G and S. It was the tv highlight of my xmas for 2019.
Oh.....BBC.....where too you going with this? 😂
snippet.textOriginal:
It was such a joy to watch....I just totally got absorbed for 1 hour.....from the scene when smiff and gavalar walk in on dawny pete pam and mick stoned out of their trees rocking around to Dreadlock Holiday to the poignant scene by Marco's with Stace giving Gavarindeeni a reality check was cracking and the Paolo Nutini song playback from their first night was a nice touch.......
The detail too like when smiff is opening presents for baby Neil in front of Nessa and she gives him a knowing look when he puts his foot down about being too young to play certain video games.  She knows Smiff is a good dad.  Did anybody spot that baby Neil had wrapped his dads present up in foil.....you just scrunch and done!
I think all fans were with pam and the gang about not liking Laura and the way she dissed his size......we dont like Laura.......
But I bet there wasnt a single fan who preficted the ending......blew me away.    Overall they did a cracking job.   Lets hope we see more G and S.   It was the tv highlight of my xmas for 2019.
Oh.....BBC.....where too you going with this?  😂
